node.text:
My “leaning into discomfort”: If you would have asked me 10 years ago (shortly after losing 100lbs) if I would ever do a boudoir shoot I would have said “HELL to the no”. My body confidence sucked, I hated the attention etc. BUT in my 30’s I’ve found a confidence I never imagined, a body that I love (curves especially) and the space to try so many new things despite the discomfort. I now embrace discomfort, I sometimes even love it. When you venture to the uncomfortable you end up with amazing things, which for me are things like these photos. Won’t post them all here bc it is still Facebook but happy to share more privately. Shout out to Kimber Greenwood with @waterbearphotography for supporting me in this "alternative" shoot! And to @karawinslowmua and @kaaypom the beauty dream team! 
#boudoir #boudoirphotography #thickwhitegirl #thick #thicknfit #honormycurves #thickthighssavelives #thicc #fitness #fit  #curvyconfidence #curvygirlsrock #boldncurvy #mirrorselfie #selfie #thickandproud #thickandcurvygoddess #gainesville

사진은 빛이 참 중요하더라.
자전거도 빛이 참 중요하더라.
겨울이라 해가 지면 춥더라.
햇살 따뜻이 비춰줄 때 타야되더라.

자전거에 빛이 내렸더라.
나도 한줄기 빛에 쏘였더라.
빛이 세상에 온 것이더라.

사진은 오래 전에 찍은거더라.
추운 줄 모르고 자전거 타던 겨울이 가더라.
봄이 오는가보더라.

자전거 탈 틈이 나질 않더라. 
자전거 타면 왠지 행복해지더라.
행복도 성취감에서 오더라.
그렇더라.
